Team,

Per our call today within the Netwrix Enterprise Auditor (NEA) and Proxy host for PALIMOMI noting that the scans Tuesday (failing) Thursday (completing) we then then followed our prior process.

Ram the following jobs
1. Jobs > Z.Sandbox > FS_DropTables   << for only the 3. Drop FSDLP Tables
2. Jobs > FileSystem > 3.Prep > 0-Create Schema
3. Manually deleted the Ter 2 *DLP* (SQLite) DBs from the NEA FSSA path as well as the Proxy host FSAA folder path.

Ernie2 noted that a DB on the Proxy was newer than on the NEA host looking at the files the only FSAADB file that did not have a matching date code was the _ProgresssFSAA.fsaadb this file was copied to the NEA host and the one in the FSAAHOST-NAME folder and the file was overwritten.

Please let me know how the next set of scans complete.

Again, thank You for your time.
